    <note>Fan(2) Yuangong [16790] His mingzi was Gui, but he used his zi, Yuangong. In 1126 he was captured by Jin and taken to Yanshan (Beijing). He later left Beijing and ended up in Fuzhou on the Inner Mongolian border where he married into the Zhe family (hereditary prefects of Fuzhou) and read all the books in the Zhe family library. Later, he attached himself to a military leader who returned to allegiance to Song and Yuangong was appointed to a military post. Li Shi, WJ, 15.17a-21a. CBD, 2, 1642.</note>
